items.title: SPS Commerce’s new tech marries AI and retail supply chain efficiency
items.content_html: The National Retail Federation predicted retail sales in November and December of 2025, will grow between 3.7% and 4.2% over 2024. That translates to total spending between $1.01 trillion and $1.02 trillion. By comparison, 2024’s holiday sales rose 4.3% over 2023 to reach $976.1 billion. While consumer demand remains strong, consumer expectation hits new heights. […] The post SPS Commerce’s new tech marries AI and retail supply chain efficiency appeared first on FreightWaves .

items.title: Rockefeller Group sells new 241,000 sq. ft. industrial building in Piscataway to Elion Partners
items.content_html: Rockefeller Group has sold a newly completed, 241,200-square-foot distribution center in Piscataway, the final piece of a redevelopment that yielded more than 2.5 million square feet of modern warehouse space over the course of a decade.
